title: Oral Roberts picked 3rd in Summit League coaches poll, Emegano chosen preseason player of year
text:
Oral Roberts picked 3rd in Summit League coaches poll, Emegano chosen preseason player of year THE ASSOCIATED PRESS   4:44 pmLast   4:44 pm   
Subjects: 
TULSA, Oklahoma â€” The Oral Roberts University men's basketball team is picked to finish third in The Summit League in a preseason poll while the Golden Eagles Obi Emegano was selected the preseason Player of the Year. 
The poll released Thursday is from voting by league sports information directors, coaches and the media. 
South Dakota State is picked to win the conference, followed by North Dakota State, ORU, Fort Wayne, South Dakota, IUPUI, Omaha, Denver and Western Illinois. 
Emegano was first team All-Summit League last season after finishing second in the conference in scoring at 18.3 points per game.
